-- Chavez Speaks From Barinas After Reports of Health Problems
-- B y   D a n i e l   C a n c e l
-- 2012-02-21T18:29:09Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-02-21/chavez-speaks-from-barinas-after-reports-of-health-problems.html
Venezuelan President  Hugo Chavez 
spoke today for the first time since Feb. 17 after a columnist
for El Universal said yesterday that he was in Cuba meeting with
a team of doctors to determine whether he needed another
operation due to his battle with cancer.  Chavez, speaking today on state television from his home
state of Barinas, said that he was spending time with his family
the last few days.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Daniel Cancel in Caracas at 
 dcancel@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Joshua Goodman at 
 jgoodman19@bloomberg.net  